New tour announcement, Join us in the ARCTIC! 

Embarking in Svalbard, home to more polar bears then people join us on a 15 day Arctic photo tour starting in the remote Norwegian archipelago voyaging through the fjords of  East Greenland & disembarking in the land of volcanos, Iceland.

With the opportunity to capture & experience an incredible amount of wildlife, big mountains, glaciers, explore Inuit villages & spend evenings under the northern lights this will be the trip of a lifetime. 

Limited spots available, get in touch for more info

Colours & shades of Namibia.

Returning early this year to lead our sold out Photo-Tour crafted from 7 years experience and a genuine love of working in one of the most incredible places on earth. 

More tour destinations within Africa & the Arctic are open for 2024, get in touch for details.

The Emperor Penguin, the most incredible yet fragile of the Penguin species are the only penguins that call Antarctica home during the winter. 

This is a few clips from the 2 days I spent with the colony here on Snow Hill Island in the Weddell Sea, a once in a life time experience.
